I am writing this note as an expression of interest in finding out more about your guild. It was suggested to me by many charachters I regularly group with in light of the intensity with which I approach my play.<br>
<br>
 I have played EQ 3 months during most of which I was a paladain. After reaching 55 with 6 AA I got bored adn re-rolled as a cleric. After 2 weeks of play I am now a 57 cleric and am spending my time in POV leading Razor and Golem camps to gain xp. Let me lay out what I am seeking and why I am seeking it,<br>
<br>
1) A consistent group of people<br>
<br>
The reality is that groups of strangers will almost inevitiablely fail to achieve thier full potential bc no one makes the commitemnt to learn about the strengths and weaknesses of those in the group. I wish to work witha group of individuals I know and trust and with whom I can explore the potential of my gereral EQ skill and that of my class.<br>
<br>
2) Knowledge<br>
<br>
The lack of knowledge in EQ is appaling. Many people are fundamentally ignorant not only of the basic abilities of all the other classes but of thier own. I do not like to waste my time on CR bc people make mistakes that are so obvious as they should be basic knnowledge(i.e USE ASSIST and do not pull a train to camp taht will wipe group) If you group with another class you should at a minimum know most of what that class can do and what the synergies are between them. It is only in this way that a group or raid for that matter can achieve its fulll potential. Even though it would be optimal way to learn, it is a waste of time to develop a charachter to 65 in each class with 100AA as much of the time is spent in monotomous xp ing that does not teach one much. It is not a waste of time for me to know HOW an Enchanter, Shaman etc can optimally fit into a group or solo such that I may fgure out how to oversome obstacles that might otherwise seem insurmountable. In order to truly be an expert in your class, you should be to the greatest degree possible an expert in every class. I want ot worl with a group of people who will explore this reality with me so that we may all learn from each other.<br>
<br>
Good Communication<br>
<br>
Good communication is also a rare commodity on FV. This may be bc roleplaying can sometimes get in the way, but it is more people do not bother. IN 50% of teh groups I have ben in as a cleric I have to get other to use or write macro explaining to group what they are doing so that I muht better do my job (i.e I do not care that youa re attempting to slow the mob. I care that the mob has been slowed so I can better feel the rhythm of damage on my tank to know where the most mana efficient point to begn my CH is) This is another feature which prevents groups and individuals from working optimally.<br>
<br>
Commitment <br>
<br>
There is nothing I detest more then in joining a group to have it disband 20 min later bc someone leaves not havin tld group how long they may stay. I spend a lot of time on EQ bc I like the challenges hunting preents. TIme spent waiting for groups to form is not that fun in most cases as others in group are not much happier to be idle as well. Nor do I like when people act selfishly to teh detriment of the groupas a whole (i.e a paladain not using LOH on an aggroed cleric to save it for themselves when that does the party not a damn bit o  good<br>
<br>
I am a very intense individual. I am i Norrath semi AFk or ate keyboard 12 hours a day as I am taking a year off b4law school after having worked 100+ hours a week for 4 years. My time as that of other is a valuable commodity that should not be wasted bc peope choose to stop learning or plan thoroughly.<br>
<br>
During Octiber I will not be consistently adventuring or hunting bc postseason baseball is my greatest love. From Nov on I am basically acvailible every night.<br>
<br>
<br>
What I am seeking seems to be congrous with the principles of your guild but that is just my impression and therefore trivial. Please let me know if theis is in fact the case and whetehr you believe with the points I have laid out would make me fit in your guild or not. Pls contact me at any time.<br>
<br>
My name in FV is Csodaszepp (lastname to be detemiined)<br>
